    describe activities, that can be be observed by a 3rd party when done by someone.
    Example: The verb "understand" is not a action verb, because you can not observe
    if a person understands something. In contrast "make an example" or "describe"
    are categorized as action words, because you can observe that the person does
    it, measure how good the person does it and get evidence if the person understands
    a topic. Other often used non-action verbs are "know", "learn". #3 Please note
